Ghana’s CPP Elects Nkrumah’s Daughter as Leader, Graphic Says

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-09-12T10:26:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/ghana-s-cpp-elects-nkrumah-s-daughter-as-leader-graphic-says.html
Samia Nkrumah, the daughter of
 Ghana ’s first president, Kwame Nkrumah, was  elected  chairman of
the Convention People’s Party, the Daily Graphic reported today.  Nkrumah’s election makes her the first female chairman of
the party founded by her father and the first female leader of a
political party in the West African nation, the Accra-based,
state-owned newspaper said. Nkrumah is the CPP’s only member of
Parliament, it reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 